{"/service/ndnp/whi/batch_whi_jarlsburg_ver01/data/sn83045293/00542868909/1930110601/0497.xml":{"full_text":"Page Five\nHOOVER AIDES\nx SLEEP ON AS\nJOBLESS GROW\nBY LAURENCE TODD.\nStaff Correspondent\nThe Federated Press\nWASHINGTON Only a super\nhuman effort by the few organized\nradicals and humanitarians and by\nthe masses of organized labor will\nbring the outgoing congress, at its\nsession this winter, seriously to\nface the emergency created by a\nyear of nationwide unemployment.\nThe national capital, after weeks\nof revivalist talk by the white\nhouse, is still fundamentally indif\nferent to \u2019the need of 20,000,000\nmen, women and children for\nmoney with which to buy food,\nclothing, fuel and other necessities\nthis winter.\nHints at Marx.\nIn the reactionary Washington\nPost appears an editorial which\nspeaks vaguely of the need for\ngreater purchasing power on the\npart of the people, as an essential\nto any return of prosperity. It sug\ngests that the workers must be able\nto buy back more of \u201cwhat is pro\nduced,\u201d so that production can go\nom\nThis approach toward Marxian\neconomics is not permitted to come\nto any point, however, and the read\ners of this anti-radical paper are\npermitted to return to their discus\nsions of prohibition and the tariff.\nExtra! Bright Idea!\nOn the morning of election day\nthe capital learned that its local\ncommittee of citizens that is co\noperating in the Hoover committee\nnetwork had had a great thought\n\u2014\u201cMass distribution of manufac\ntured goods and mass consumption\nare the essentials in aiding mass\nproduction toward relief of unem\nployment.\u201d\nJust who would pay for the\ngoods that were to be distributed\nand consumed in mass by the\nmasses was not discussed.\nThe local committee\u2019s spokesmen\nrested on the declaration that the\npeople at large must receive and\nconsume more goods: \u201cIt is not\nenough that wages and consump\ntion standards shall keep pace with\nthe capacity of society to produce,\nso that production may not outrun\npurchasing power and thus create a\nsystem of mass underconsumption,\nwhere many are still inadequately\nhoused, meanly clothed and under\nnourished.\u201d\nBoring From Within.\nThat sounds like a Socialist bor\ning from within a frightened com\nmittee of unemployed realtors and\nmerchants. It is good economics\nand sound sense. But it has no\nteeth. It gives not the slightest\nhint as to how, when and where\nthis altruism is to be crystallized\ninto action in congress or in any\nstate or city. It is no more useful\nin feeding tenement dwellers in\nPittsburgh than are Portuguese an\nti-slavery laws in stopping whole\nsale slavery in the Portuguese\ncolonies in Africa.\nIt does not name any step that\nthis district committee will take to\nforce appropriations from congress.\nThere are rumblings of a growing\ndisgust among the unemployed,\neven in non-industrial Washington,\nwith the lack of action from the\nwhite house. By the time congress\nconies back to town, to pass the an\nnual $700,000,000 of appropriations\nfor military defense of the most\npowerful nation on earth, this re\nsentment may have ripened into\nmass action of some sort.\nMay Disturb Poker Gaines.\nThere may be a march of the\nunemployed past the white house\nor into the guarded grounds of the\ncapitol, with placards demanding\nbread and shelter. There may be\nfiery speeches at street corners.\nThere may, on the other hand, be\nnothing of the sort, but a continued\nsilence in which the federal office\nholders can resume their poker\ngames.\nChances are, however, that the\nNorris group will propose, in the\nDecember session, that some of the\nvast sums usually devoted to the\narmy and navy be diverted this\nwinter to keeping 20,000,000 Amer\nicans from starving and freezing.\n500 Million Annual\nFuel Damage, Waste\nNEW YORK Improper combus\ntion of fuels in heating and power\nplants and soft coal smoke causes\ndamage amounting to more than\n$500,000,000 a year in the United\nStates, it is reported by the fuel\nresearch laboratories. New York\ncity alone pays $96,000,000 of the\ndamage.\nReligion vs. Science,\nIs Topic of Debate\nIs Religion Opposed to Science?\nwill be the question of a debate at\na meeting of the Open Mind, a\nyoung men\u2019s discssion club, at 8\ntonight at the Y. M. C. A. The\naffirmative speaker will be Isadore\nSedet; negative, Philip Cohn.\nBOYS! HERE\u2019S HIKE.\nAll boys are invited to join a\nhike to the Agricultural school\nwoods, Wauwatosa, Saturday. Mait\nland Cook will lead the hike from\nthe Y. M. C. A. boys\u2019 building at\n1 p. m.\ntL\n\\~Zc\\\nWhen the clock reads 4--\n1H HIGH TIME TO POUrW_\nA CLASS of p\nS\u2014 1 IL .i\nd_Li ul l 8 8\n(C) 1930. M. D. c.\nTWO MILWAUKEE YOUTHS WILL\nMANAGE N. Y. HOTEL FOR A DAY\nCommoners have been kings for\na day and Boy Scouts have offici\nated as mayors of large cities for\nthe same period, but it remains for\ntwo Milwaukee boys, both attend\ning Cornell university, Ithaca, N.\nY., to become jointly the managing\ndirector of one of New York\u2019s fore\nmost hostelries from dawn until\ndusk.\nErnst Clarenbach, Jr., son of\nErnst Clarenbach, 1045 Shepard\nave., and Ray Smith, Jr., son of the\nowner of the Pfister hotel, will as\nsume the management of the New\nYorker hotel Monday.\nGERMAN LABOR\nSEES 40-HOUR\nWEEK ESSENTIA!\nBy Federated Press.\nBERLlN\u2014Demand that the Ger\nman parliament established by law\na 40-hour work week to relieve un\nemployment, has been made by the\ngeneral council of the German Fed\nration of Trade Unions, after a ses-\nsion devoted to the economic depres\nsion.\nTheodore Leipart, president of\nthe federation, in a speech outlin\ning the reasons for this demand,\nsaid that \u201cwe had meant to wait\nuntil trade should again be good\nbefore demanding still shorter\nhours than the 44-hour week de\nmanded at the Stockholm congress\nof the International Federation of\nTrade Unions.\nBecomes Necessary Now.\n\u201cBut now we are forced to deal\nwith this question during a trade\ndepression. What was once the\nfruit of our growing economic ac\ntivities is now become a measure\ncalled for by bitter necessity.\n\u201cToday the worker in a factory\ndoes not even know whether he will\nbe at work on the morrow. A short\nening of working hours means,\ntherefore, a kind of self-insurance\nof the workers against further dis\nmissals, and, besides this, an act of\nsolidarity towards the unemployed.\u2019\u2019\nTo Relieve Labor Market.\nThe resolution adopted calls for\nthe 40-hour work week \u201cuntil the\nlabor market is relieved of its pres\nent congestion, such 40-hour week\nto be accompanied by a general ob\nligation to put on more workers in\nproportion to the shortening of\nworking hours, to notify vacancies\nand to make use of the public labor\nexchanges.\n\u201cThe funds hitherto used as un\nemployment benefit may be utilized\nto help compensate for the in\ncreased wages bill during the tran\nsition period. Permits for overtime\nwork must be limited to the most\nurgent exceptional cases, and it\nmust be laid down that for every\nhour of overtime the employer shall\npay a full day\u2019s wage as a special\ncontribution to the unemployment\nbenefit fund.\u201d\nSCIENCE PLANS\nPRODUCTION OF\nMENTAL GIANTS\nPALO ALTO, Calif.\u2014ln the not\ndistant future science may turn its\nattention to production of intellec\ntual giants and geniuses, in the\nopinion of Dr. Lewis M. Terman,\nbend of the Stanford university\ndepartment of psychology.\nThis conclusion is embodied in\nthe third volume of a series of\nGenetic Studies of Genius.\nThe researchers found that girl\nprodigies do not maintain their\nsuperiority in adolescence to the ex\ntent that boys of the \u201cgenius\ngroup\u201d do, but tend to revert to\nthe average in mental ability.\nSays We\u2019re Al! Crazy.\nCHlCAGO\u2014Everybody is crazy,\nand it is only a matter of degree\nwhether a person is inside an asy\nlum or not.\nThat was the encouraging word\npassed out yesterday by Prof. John\nMorgan of the Northwestern uni\nversity psychology department dur\ning a talk on the Abnormal Mind.\nHe said:\n\u201cThere are three elements of in\nsanity in every person which can\nbreak forth to \u2018case\u2019 proportions at\nany time. They are day-dreaming,\nrationalizing and a complex toward\ninferiority.\u201d\nThe ability to face reality Is the\nkeynote of sanity, the professor as\nserted.\nTUNE IN WTMJ\nTonite. 7:30 to 8\nBETTY JANE RADIO PARTY\nCANDIES (BXO\nAT ALL CANDY DEALERS\nThey will have charge of both\nthe credit and ojieration of the 43-\nstory hostelry, under the supervi\nsion of Ralph Hitz, managing direc\ntor.\nThis opportunity to \u201cw\u2019atch the\nwheels go around\u201d in a hotel,\nwhere more than 70,000 guests are\naccommodated every month, and\nwhere in the first 10 months of its\nfirst year more than 500,000 Amer\nicans registered, is given each year\nto members ot the junior class of\nthe Cornell university hotel school.\nBoth youths are 21 years old,\nboth are graduates of Milwaukee\nCountry Day school, and both will\nreceive their diplomas from Cor\nnell in 1923.\nThey will participate in the ac\ntivities of the national hotel ex\nposition in New York next week.\na new improved\nCORONA\nWaffle Iron\nwith heat Indicator\n\u2022Hr\nBetter than ever. A perfect\nwaffle baker. Makes any\nvariety of waffles equally\nwell. You\u2019ll enjoy using it.\nSpecially priced at\n$7.45\n45c Down\nSI.OO a Month\nCORONA Heatins Pad\nIt affords prompt relief from\nincipient colds, aches and\npains, often preventing ser\nious illness. This Corona, 3\nheat pad, is dependable.\npriced\nkw\u00df\nonly\n$5.85\nElectric Egg Cooker\n\nSteam cooks eggs just\nas you like them\n$5.50\nThe Hamilton Beach\nElectric Cleaner\nAwonderful\ncleaner at a rea\nsonable price.\nn\n$2.75\nDown Ml\n$2.75 I\na A Month\nMoth wfipl\nExpello jISSt\nFree .o\u00dfbl\nwith Xj9^^\nAttachments\nThe Electric Hand Cleaner\nMarvelous Suction\n$13.50\nAttachments Moth Expello\n$3.00\npqa\nBringing The Sun\nInto The Home\nChildren and adults, too. ean gain\nwonderful benefits from this amax\ning indoor sun\u2014Hanovia Alpine\nSun Lamp\u2014bodies grow stronger,\nhandsomer metabolism is stim\nulated\u2014and new vigor is created\nto resist the menaces of modern\nindoor life.\nSee Demonstration On Our Sales\nFloor.\nThe ELECTRIC\nCOMPANY\nMichigan at Second St.\nBRANCH SALESROOMS at\nWauwatosa\u20142l6 No. Main St.\nCudahy\u2014llo3 Packard Ave.\nWest Allis\u2014so 4 63rd Ave.\nSo. Milwaukee\u20142lll 10th Ave.\nNo. Milwaukee\u201436os Villard Ave\nL\u2014\u2014\nTHE MILWAUKEE LEADER, THURSDAY, NOVEMBER 6, 1930\nOur Hostess\nDepartment Has\na Birthday\nSix years ago, recognizing that our cus\ntomers would welcome a more personal\ncontact with the Boston Store, we insti\ntuted this service.\nOur Hostesses provide friendly helpful*\nness to you and out-of-town shoppers.\nThey are ready to shop with or for you,\nand to advise, if you so desire.\nMany Milwaukee women use the Hostess\nstaff, realizing that thorough knowledge\nof the store and its merchandising makes\nfor efficient shopping.\nMen, too, who have little or no time to\nshop, are among its many patrons.\nAs in all our hundred-odd departments,\nthe Hostess service is prepared to meet\nyour needs.\n^Governor\nW inthrop 77\nSecretary\nIS i\nThe \u201cGovernor\nWinthrop\u201d secre- I\ntary is a quality [^^^^B l 9\np iece of f urn i- J=. 9^^^^\nture that will\nmeet with the ap\nproval of the\nmost critical 1\nbuyer. -BL\nOur Comparison\nDepartment reports\nthat similar secre-\ntarles sell for $59\nto $69 elsewhere in S\u00ae\nMilwaukee all\nof which goes to\nprove that. Indeed,\n\u201cQanllty considered,\nwe are seldom nn\ndersold.\u201d W- H\n4.50 DOWN,\nBalance 9\nMonthly, If\nIf You Wisli\nBoston Store\u2014Furniture\u2014Fourth Floor\u2014South\nAsk for \u201cS&H\u201d Stamps\nBoy\nScouts,\nWOK. J-v Attention!\nChief Whirling Thunder\nWill Be at the Davidson Theater Sat\nurday, Nov. Bth, at 10 o\u2019Clock A. M.\nA specially prepared program of interest to all Boy\nScouts, featuring the appearance of Chief Whirling\nThunder of the Winnebago Tribe, instructor of\nwood carving and sign language at Culver Military\nAcademy. He will be dressed in full Indian Cos\ntume, and will be assisted by Scouts.\nGeneral Outline of Program Given\nby Chief Whirling Thunder\nI\u2014Winnebago Greeting Song\n2\u2014Pipe Ceremony\n3\u2014Life of the Northern Indian\n4\u2014Dances Warrior's Dance; War\nDance; Squaw Dance and others\ns\u2014How to Camp\n6\u2014lndian Sign Language\n7\u2014 Legends\nB\u2014Games, Mocassin Game and Bone\nGame\n9\u2014How stone arrowheads are made\n10\u2014Songs with story\n11\u2014Legend\nBoy Scouts, secure your admission tickets this week\nwithout charge at the Boy Scout Trading Post,\nThird Floor, North, Boston Store. Be sure to bring\nyour scout identification card.\nBOSJHrE\n^The^eart ofZ^Glwauhee^\nMEMBER AMERICAN RETAILERS, INCORPORATED\nI\nHooked Rug Materials,\nBear Brand Yarns O\nSpecial purchase sale of the very things you I I yQk V yZ\nneed for making Christmas gifts of yarn. I\nStandard Knitting Worsted Bucilla Hooked Rug Yam\nBlack, white and colors. Complete color assortments, OPz, /I Q\nLarge size skein VUv 27-yard skein, each mOC |1 Ml\nBucilla Hooked Rug Patterns\nPopular patterns, large sizes, mostly 30x54 in. Would QQ n to 1 QK\nsell in a regular way for 1.35 to 1.98, at vOL *C\nBear Brand Yarns Bucilla Rug Patterns k\n38c Germantown ball 29c. R 59 t 47c R 89cat 78c M ||W\n38c Saxony, ball 32c. no Q _ D o _ nc M\n55c Knitting Worsted, 42c. at s 7c at $2 H\n27c Shetland Floss, 22c. Reg. 2.25 at 1.98 Reg. 3.50 at 2.95\n57c Artwool, at 47c. Reg. 4.75 at 3.95\nBoston Store-\u2014Art Goods\u2014Third Floor\u2014Center Ask for \u201cS&H\u201d Stamps\nMake Your Own\nComforts Now\nMany women prefer to make their own comforts be\ncause they wish!them 